   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>B. Issuing In Jehovah's Restoration</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Jehovah's punishment of Ephraim issued in His restoration.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Jehovah Becoming a Crown</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>of Glory and a Diadem of Beauty</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>In the day of restoration, Jehovah will become a crown of glory and a diadem of beauty to the remnant of His people v. 5 .</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Jehovah Becoming a Spirit of Justice</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Jehovah will become a spirit of justice for him who sits in judgment and strength to those who turn away the battle at the gate v. 6 .</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>C. Ushering In the Trustworthy Christ</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Jehovah's punishment over Ephraim's drunkards will also usher in the trustworthy Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>1.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>A Stone Laid by the Lord Jehovah in Zion</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The trustworthy Christ is a stone laid by the Lord Jehovah in Zion as a foundation, a tested stone.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Because Christ has been tested, He can be a foundation v. 16a .</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>A Precious Cornerstone</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The trustworthy Christ is also a precious cornerstone as a foundation firmly established v. 16b . In Matthew 21:42 the Lord Jesus refers to Himself as the cornerstone.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Furthermore, both Paul and Peter speak of Christ as a cornerstone.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>In Ephesians 2:20 Paul says that in building up the two parts of God's building, the Jews and the Gentiles, Christ Jesus Himself is the cornerstone.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>In Acts 4:11 Peter says, "This is the stone which was despised by you, the builders, which has become the cornerstone."</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Later, in his first Epistle, Peter says, "To whom coming, a living stone, having been rejected by men, but with God chosen, held in honor" 2:4 .</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>The One Believing Not Hastening Away</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Isaiah 28:16c says that he who believes will not hasten away.</S>
   </TEXT>
